core::result::Result::<T, E>::is_ok.doc:
Returns `true` if the result is [`Ok`].

# Examples

```
let x: Result<i32, &str> = Ok(-3);
assert_eq!(x.is_ok(), true);

let x: Result<i32, &str> = Err("Some error message");
assert_eq!(x.is_ok(), false);
```

